cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of obtaining network coding maps for wireless bidirectional relaying, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of graphs and vertex coloring to represent the singularity removal constraints, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves wireless communication and networking, which could fall under the categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Latin Squares, which could fall under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
